messages.subject: Re: [Unschooling-dotcom] aeroplane jelly
messages.msgSnippet: ... can t help you with the jelly thing.  Mum did have a lillypilly tree in the front yard though and I used to eat them.  Funny things.  Not blue but a pinky
messages.messageBody:
>>Sorry Sandra,
can't help you with the jelly thing. Mum did have a lillypilly tree in the front yard though and I used to eat them. Funny things. Not blue but a pinky colour and really light (as in not heavy) and about the size of a cherry<g> I remember that they made my teeth feel 'dirty' yep, had a 'nothing' taste but a bit like dirt LOL I don't know what I mean LOL Wish I could send you some but I haven't seen a lilly pilly tree for years.<<

Lee-Ann in Harrow, Victoria, Australia, The World :)

We have a lilly pilly tree growing at our place but I think it is still to small to fruit. I have never eaten them. I'll have a close look at the jelly when I go shopping today and see it there is any mysterious, blue jelly on the shelves!

Julie

Sorry Sandra,
can't help you with the jelly thing. Mum did have a lillypilly tree in the front yard though and I used to eat them. Funny things. Not blue but a pinky colour and really light (as in not heavy) and about the size of a cherry<g> I remember that they made my teeth feel 'dirty' yep, had a 'nothing' taste but a bit like dirt LOL I don't know what I mean LOL Wish I could send you some but I haven't seen a lilly pilly tree for years.

Lee-Ann in Harrow, Victoria, Australia, The World :)
